<subSubSection pageId="34" pageNumber="661" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="34.[1387,2590,3045,3357]" pageId="34" pageNumber="661">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lonnberg" authorityYear="1919" box="[1389,1506,3081,3114]" class="Mammalia" family="Cercopithecidae" genus="Papio" kingdom="Animalia" order="Primates" pageId="34" pageNumber="661" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="kindae">P. kindae</taxonomicName>
has previously been considered a subspecies of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1766" box="[2167,2363,3081,3114]" class="Mammalia" family="Cercopithecidae" genus="Papio" kingdom="Animalia" order="Primates" pageId="34" pageNumber="661" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="cynocephalus">P. cynocephalus</taxonomicName>
. It is recognized here as a full species because it is as morphologically and genetically distinctive as the five other baboon species. Furthermore, preliminary behavioral observations suggest significant differences compared with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1766" box="[1991,2188,3198,3231]" class="Mammalia" family="Cercopithecidae" genus="Papio" kingdom="Animalia" order="Primates" pageId="34" pageNumber="661" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="cynocephalus">P. cynocephalus</taxonomicName>
. This species hybridizes with P. wrsinus griseipes and P. c. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1766" box="[1760,1922,3242,3271]" class="Mammalia" family="Cercopithecidae" genus="Papio" kingdom="Animalia" order="Primates" pageId="34" pageNumber="661" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="cynocephalus">cynocephalus</taxonomicName>
in respective contact zones in Zambia.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="34" pageNumber="661" type="multiple">
<caption inLine="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="661" targetBox="[183,763,303,710]" targetPageId="35">
<paragraph blockId="34.[1387,2590,3045,3357]" pageId="34" pageNumber="661">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1389,1564,3277,3310]" pageId="34" pageNumber="661">Distribution.</emphasis>
Extreme SW Tanzania (possibly N to Mahale Mountains National Park), S DR Congo, W Zambia (W of Luangwa River), and N Angola.
</paragraph>
</caption>
</subSubSection>
